Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present 123 Midson Road, Epping. 123 Midson Road Is a two storey freehold commercial property positioned conveniently amongst a central group of local shops. The property boasts a significant 1,017sqm* land offering and a total floor area of 1,083sqm* across four ground floor retail shops and four first floor offices. In addition, there are 22 car spaces on the lower ground floor level. The favourable zoning of the site allows discerning purchasers the exciting opportunity to create a future mixed-use development (STCA). 123 Midson Road is located in the heart of Epping, directly next to Eileen Mahoney Park and within close proximity to well-ranked schools, shops and other amenities. The property is easily accessible with bus services within 100m* and Epping Railway within 1km*, allowing for easy travel to Chatswood, Parramatta CBD and Sydney CBD.


123 Midson Road, Epping benefits from the following key attributes:

- 8 retail/office suites & 22 car spaces
- 1,017sqm* site area
- 1,083sqm* floor area
- Prime location less than 1km* from Epping Town Centre & Epping Railway
- Favourable planning controls allowing for future mixed-use development (STCA)
- Great accessibility moments to bus, train and metro services to Chatswood, Parramatta CBD and Sydney CBD

123 Midson Road, Epping is offered For Sale via Private Treaty. Price - $7,900,000.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:

12 - 22 Langston Place is within walking distance to shops, schools, Epping CBD Plaza, public transport (Epping train and bus stations).

- Land Area: 6,899sqm* with FSR of 6:1 and height limit of 72m

                                                                                   *approximate

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: RESIDENTIAL / MIXED USE DEVELOPMENT SITE WITH HOLDING INCOME

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Gross Floor Area of up to 38,700sqm*

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE have been exclusively appointed by Landcom and Sydney Metro to market 242-244 Beecroft Road, Epping, which is an approved, mixed use development site.

Epping is a well-regarded and popular Northern Sydney suburb.

The site has an approved Concept State Significant Development Application (SSD 8784) with building envelopes for three mixed use towers, with a maximum height of 48 metres each. 

The approval is for a maximum Gross Floor Area of up to 38,700sqm*, comprising up to 37,700sqm of residential and between 750sqm and 1,000sqm of retail/commercial floor area.

Key Features:
•	Concept State Significant Development Application
•	Land Area of 10,137sqm*
•	Gross Floor Area of up to 38,700sqm*
•	R4 High Density Residential Zoning
•	Building height limit up to 48 metres
•	Within 300 metres* of Epping Station
•	Dual Street frontages

* approximate

This development opportunity is being offered via a single stage tender.

All Tenders are submitted electronically to Landcom’s Tender Portal at tenders.landcom.com.au by 5pm on Friday, 12th March 2021.
